    • getCommandDisplaySuffixes

      protected String[] getCommandDisplaySuffixes()
      Returns the parameters hint to display as an array of Strings. These strings are displayed after the command name in the autocomplete suggestions for this command to indicate to the user what each parameter means.

    • getCommandDisplaySuffix

      protected abstract String getCommandDisplaySuffix()
      Returns the parameter hint to display after the command name, before parameter entry has started. This string is displayed after the command name in the autocomplete suggestion for this command before the user has entered a command, in order to indicate to the user what parameters they will have to enter.

    • addParameterSuggestions

      protected abstract void addParameterSuggestions(String[] parsedString, List<AutocompleteResult> returnList, boolean isMidParameter)
      Adds autocomplete suggestions for this command.
      Parameters:
      parsedString - The text entered by the user so far in the QuickJump box, split on spaces.
      returnList - A list to which this method should add the appropriate autocomplete suggestions.
      isMidParameter - True if the user is in the middle of typing a parameter.

    • trailingSpaceSuggestions

      protected List<AutocompleteResult> trailingSpaceSuggestions(String textSoFar, String[] parsedTextSoFar)
      Suggestions to be returned when the text so far ends with a space, so the user is about to type an argument to the command. Most commands can use the default implementation, which uses getCommandDisplaySuffixes() to display a single suggestion appropriate to the level. But specialized commands can add to this default behavior.
      Parameters:
      textSoFar - the text the user has typed so far
      parsedTextSoFar - the same text, split on the space character
      Returns:
      a newly created mutable list of possibilities.
